rComments: Took this prof this summer, was hands down the worst prof I have ever had. He was extremely unprofessional and offensive, and he gave no feedback on assignments.

Overall confusing! There's no other way to describe the course, he expects you to know the lectures, the slides, and the textbook, all of which are different. "My opinion is the right one" is an actual thing he said at the beginning of the semester. Papers are online assignments were easy, but he doesn't prepare you for the final at all.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Lots of homework', 'Lecture heavy']

rComments: Horrible, horrible prof for this class. Lectures made no sense and half the time it was hard to follow what he was saying. Felt like when he spoke he belittled us. He also gave no guidelines for the final, which was the whole semester and worth half your grade.

I really enjoyed taking his course "international finance" because he doesn't just purely talk about the class material, which is solely based on the textbook. In my opinion he does a great job connecting the course theory with current events, which makes it very interesting. Grading: 80% midterm+final, 20% term paper.

Would avoid this prof at all costs. Assignments are fair, albeit a little unclear. However, lectures don't appear to follow any sort of logic, and the lack of midterm makes preparing for the final essentially impossible. Furthermore, in class he is sometimes harsh with students who don't know the answers to his questions.

Best Prof at uOttawa. Unfortunately he got into a bike accident and we missed 2 classes but despite the accident he still wanted to teach the class which speaks volumes about this man. Very fair grader and very approachable if you need clarifications. The midterms and exams are the same numbers that are at the end of the textbook so do them.

Professor Sharma convinced me to pursue economics in graduate studies in one lecture. If you're of the mindset that economics is an uncontestable science in which debate is useless, he is not who you are looking for. I personally appreciated the fact that he went out of his way to challenge commonly held ideas--unlike other profs, he made me think!

This prof is a really nice guy, but I do find his lectures go off on too much of a tangent. I feel like I taught myself most of the course. Overall, it was a mediocre experience. Word of advice: do the textbook questions because he uses them for tests!
Boring !!!!

These class presentations are peer graded so no blame on prof. This prof is great if you want to understand and connect what happens in reality with class material.  Easy summer A and I enjoyed discussing the Greek debt crisis in relation to growth theory. He is unclear with evaluation but that's because its easy and he's liberal with marking.
One of the worst professors at Uottawa . I did not learn anything when I took eco2143 with him . He assigns group presentations  which he marks harshly on . Do not take a class with this guy .

By far the worst teacher I have had out of over 30 professors. He spends much of class on tangents, his group presentations were useless and took up half of his "teaching" time, and if you want any hope in passing you need him to like you and you need to only focus solely on the textbook. Don't dare give him feedback or he'll get overly defensive.

Don't. Just don't. This was a summer class for me, and we had 3 hour lectures twice a week for 6 weeks. Half the lectures were spent on presentations by students (which replace midterms btw), and the other half discussing current events. I learnt nothing about macroeconomics. Had to study all the material on my own for the final.

Even though he really knew what he was talking about, he was somewhat rude whenever people would ask questions and sort of laugh when people didn't understand what he said. Easy class overall, just two midterms and an exam, all multiple choice. The textbook had a workbook with a lot of good practice questions which saved my life. Accent is thick.

HE IS AN AMAZING PROF! ASK HIM WHAT YOU NEED; HE WILL HELP YOU! HE IS A PRACTICAL GUY. He is on point. to better understand the application of the topic on real world, it is better for you to get involved in class discussions. class participation is not mandatory and he doesn't pick on students, though it is helpful to be in class.

Attendance is not mandatory but his classes are fun. Very approachable, helpful and friendly.  Gives good feedback on any subject matter. He is definitely one of the profs who wants you to get an A+ and succeed. Dont base your entire judgement from one negative comment. Find out for yourself.  Great guy!!!!
nice, and funny. Class is easy and his lectures notes are really complete ( thats why textbook is not nescessary)

Doesn't use a textbook, lectures are unorganized and thoughtless. Contradicts himself, and other profs. Goes off on tangents that are not related to course material whatsoever and then when he falls behind on lectures students must catch up on their own time. Content of the course could be very interesting, but due to his teaching style it was not

Sharma is an awful prof. He is extremely rude to all students and his lectures are confusing. The 3 multiple choice midterms and mc final are based entirely on the textbook, do not go to class because his lectures will just confuse you. Follow the textbook and review questions and you'll be fine

He's a great guy. He takes the time to get the class involved and to relate the material to the real world. His tests are very fair and if someone is willing to put the effort in, they can definitely get a good mark.
Do not take a class with him

Very bad teacher, poor communication skills and often times rude to students. Does not rely on text books but rather his "parables". ABSOLUTELY NOTHING taught was on the midterms or finals or from the text book. Waste of time and money, I would avoid this teacher at all costs. I have not a single clue how he became a university professor. 2/10.

He is awful. No respect for students, refuses to answer questions regarding midterms, and tests. Contradicts other profs. Lectures did not follow course outline in any way. Potential to be a very informative course but ruined by his arrogance
He's all over the place with his lectures and argumentative with students who ask questions. The midterm contained things that we never once covered in class. Avoid this prof.

Terrible. He gave us extra assignments. first one worth 2 marks = 15 questions with sections till G. second assignment work 1 mark and 9 questions. AVOID HIM AT ALL COSTS HE IS HORRIBLE I don't know why the University still allows him to teach. No respect for his students at all either.  talks down about other profs, and  is "not an academic"

Do not bother going to class. Invest in the textbook and self-teach. 3 midterms and they're all multiple choice, but still difficult. Final exam is also multiple choice. The few times I did go to his 3 hour lectures he basically just rambled on. Did not provide any clarity to the material.

Very interesting class. I learned a lot. He is very knowledgable and encourages engaging in thoughtful discussions on class material using real-life examples, which are conducive to understanding the class material. He does not go on about David Suzuki, his English is in no way hard to understand, he is not at all arrogant, etc. Great teacher.

Avoid this prof st all costs. He is extremely arrogant, doesn't answer questions basically just argues back with students. For some reason he hates David Suzuki and seems to bring it up every class. He demands answers from students even though no one knows whats going on. AVOID AVOID AVOID

Really arrogant prof, but knows his stuff. Lectures are confusing as he jumps around in the content, and he doesn't clarify which chapters he is covering in the lecture. Read the textbook to learn content. Often rambles and is demeaning to students who ask questions. Midterms are all multiple choice, but still difficult.

Rude and condescending, his 3 hour class is actually a 3 hour rant filled with "parables" and statements that what he knows is what is right. I just go and read the textbook. For the exam in which I received 94% I didn't once review his notes (not that I had any), I just read the textbook.

AVOID AT ALL COSTS. He uses useless examples, goes on and on about David Suzuki ruining the world, very hard to understand, and don't you dare ask a question cause he might just say, " that's a stupid question, put your hand down". If in his course, skip the lecture. Learn from the textbook and his problems sets. You'll do fine.

OMG the best prof ever. I was enrolled in Eco 2142 over summer and basically had to go through the whole course in about a month or so. This prof was very reasonable in terms of grading. But what struck me the most was clear expectation for final exam and midterms. This prof will place heavy emphasis during lectures on what will be covered in test.

Awful professor. He seems nice but does not cover the material necessary to advance to the next course and if you ask him for help on any material you may have missed, he refuses. Very rude as well when you go see him during office hours. Avoid at all costs if you can.

ok to take his ECO 1104,but do not take his ECO 2144. It is very hard to a full time student because too many questions from the book.(around 15 question each chapter)however,He is only going to test 4 question in each midterm and final.you can image you have great opportunity to meet a question that you never prepare.then at least 25 points lost.

Awesome Prof. Very fair assessments and don't get discouraged because he will give you your mark on your exam and is always looking to help his students. Keep working hard and you will do well. Excellent prof!
Best prof I had during the whole 4 years. Super knowledgeable and engaging! Very clear on what to expect on assessments. Does expect students to do work, but is highly rewarding.
Excellent prof! Very knowledgeable and very clear of what to expect on assessments! HIGHLY RECOMMEND!
Avoid this prof at all costs.

Difficult professor to follow, it's difficult to know what's on midterms as his midterms usually ask 3 questions. Sure his questions are similar to the hw, but there is so many different kinds of questions! So if you don't know 1.. well tough luck!
He's an amazing teacher, very underappreciated. He is always open to questions and very passionate about what he's teaching.

The class was good, to get a good mark you def. need to attend classes.  His examples were easy to follow, but if you fall behind it will be difficult to follow.  The study guide was very useful for this class.

Although I got a good grade, his teachings are very hard to understand. He still takes notes on the board, and i felt it was hard to keep up to his craziness. I honestly suggest you not to chose this proff! Stress for nothing. He made a mistake and gave me an F as a final grade, I end up emailing him and he made a mistake! I got a B+. From F to B+.

Content is challenging but if you do the work and read ahead, you will be okay. Prof. Sharma is interesting to listen to but tends to fall behind and in our section covered a lot in the last lecture. Notes given in class where a tad disorganized. Class attendance is important in this course.

Very good prof. Just need to do the work; it's not the easiest subject, but it will come back time and time again. Very fun personality to learn from, and gives deep insight into the logic and deeper workings of economic theory and now it would apply in the big picture: for a microeconomics prof I found him to be quite good.

An excellent prof. Will put off people who expect to be babied. He expects students to work hard, but if you do the work, you'll do fine and you'll learn something that will carry over to your other classes. Math is math. And yes, he's oppinionated, but agreeing with him is not a class requirement. Do the work. That's all he asks.

Good prof. Learned a lot in this class. Sure, he's oppinionated, but he won't sink a student for personally disagreeing with him. His requirements are clear and he expects you to work hard. If you do the work, you'll do well. Otherwise, he's not going to care and I can't say I blame him. At this level, students shouldn't be babied.
Terrible, terrible. I was in introduction to macroeconomics, NOT "how Trudeau messed up Canada." We learned NOTHING from him, a total waste of time!

Horrible prof. Cant understand his accent, rambles on with stupid arrogant comments. Class is a complete waste of time. Luckily all notes are given online and striaght out of the text so class is completely unnecessary. Got a B+ and didnt go to a full class beyond the first night(learned my lesson). Horrible horrible prof.
Not clear at explanations. Confuses the hell out of you. Follow the Textbook, do the study guide questions and study on your own. Class attendance is useless.

horrible prof. Disorganized course. Every class he would begin without informing students of what chapter he was lecturing about..and what ch. the midterms went up till. Basically stay home and teach yourself! thats what i had to do! If you can, change profs asap!

I can understand how alot of people do not like this guy, but if you actually choose to pay attention and study you can pull of a 96% like me and really get to like the guy. One thing, when he starts, hes quiet and unenthusiastic, but give him a few minutes and some questions to exicte him and after that hes hilarious and really into the material
